            "answer_text": "\u201cCar\u201d means FOR, (In the sense of Because) and \u201cParce que\u201d means BECAUSE. Eg: \u201c Il faut des parapluies, CAR il va pleuvoir\u201d. But equally Parce que can be used in the same way eg: \u201cil faut des parapluies, PARCE QU\u2019il va pleuvoir \u201c. There is one curious use of \u201cParce que\u201d. If a person is asked a question that he doesn\u2019t want to answer, he can say simply: \u201cParce que!\u201d, without any further explanations\u2026 ",
